To connect Quizlish to **Supabase** for database and authentication management, follow these steps:

### 1. Link the Supabase CDN
Add the official Supabase JavaScript SDK CDN inside the `<head>` or before the script files in [index.html](file:///g:/quizlish/index.html):

```html
<script src="https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/@supabase/supabase-js@2"></script>
```

---

### 2. Initialize the Supabase Client
In the script section of your [index.html](file:///g:/quizlish/index.html), initialize the Supabase client using your project API credentials:

```javascript
const supabaseUrl = 'https://your-project-ref.supabase.co';
const supabaseKey = 'your-anon-key'; // Found in Project Settings > API
const supabase = supabase.createClient(supabaseUrl, supabaseKey);
```

---

### 3. Replace Local Mock Auth with Real Auth APIs
Update your authentication functions to call Supabase Auth APIs:

#### **Sign Up (Registration)**
Replace simulated registration logic inside `handleAuthSubmit`:
```javascript
async function signUpUser(email, password, name) {
    const { data, error } = await supabase.auth.signUp({
        email: email,
        password: password,
        options: {
            data: {
                display_name: name
            }
        }
    });
    return { data, error };
}
```

#### **Sign In (Login)**
Replace simulated login inside `handleAuthSubmit`:
```javascript
async function signInUser(email, password) {
    const { data, error } = await supabase.auth.signInWithPassword({
        email: email,
        password: password
    });
    return { data, error };
}
```

#### **Sign Out**
Replace `handleSignOut` logic:
```javascript
async function handleSignOut() {
    const { error } = await supabase.auth.signOut();
    if (!error) {
        alert('Successfully signed out!');
    }
}
```

---

### 4. Listen to Auth State Changes Automatically
Supabase provides an listener that notifies your app whenever a login, signup, or logout happens. You can hook this up directly to the `syncAuthState()` function:

```javascript
supabase.auth.onAuthStateChange((event, session) => {
    const navBtn = document.getElementById('auth-nav-btn');
